  "prompt": "How long does it take to get an Australia PR visa in general?",
  "response": "The processing time for an Australian Permanent Residency (PR) visa can vary depending on several factors:\n\n1. Visa Subclass:\n- Skilled Migration (189/190/491): Generally 8-12 months\n- Family Sponsored: 4-6 months\n- Business/Investment Visas: Can take 12-18 months\n\n2. Factors Affecting Processing Time:\n- Completeness of application\n- Documentation accuracy\n- Background checks\n- Current immigration workload\n- Specific visa stream requirements\n\n3. Average Processing Times:\n- Most skilled migration visas: 6-15 months\n- Some visas might take up to 18-24 months in complex cases\n\n4. Additional Considerations:\n- COVID-19 has impacted processing times\n- Individual case complexity varies\n- Regular policy changes can affect timelines\n\n5. Best Practices:\n- Submit accurate and complete documentation\n- Ensure you meet all eligibility criteria\n- Use certified translations\n- Respond promptly to any requests\n\nKeep in mind that these are approximate timeframes, and individual experiences can differ. It's recommended to check the official Department of Home Affairs website for the most current information.",
